scopecontent.p:
James Norfold Pope was a 1966 grraduate of the UVa School of Medicine. His
                 caricatures are compiled in a folder which has the inscription "To Dr. Guerrant
                 with kindest regards and no rhinitis J N Pope '66." In order, the caricatures are
                 David C. Smith; Oliver Beirne Bobbitt Jr.; John M. Nokes ???; Eugene A. Foster;
                 Martin G. Netsky; Chalmers Laughlin Gemmill; Molly: unknown woman; Gene and Molly:
                 unknown; Calvin M. Kunin; George: unknown; Gerald Goldstein; Wild Bill: unknown;
                 Andrew D. Hart; Elton Meredith Alrich; C. Bruce Morton; James Edwin Wood Jr.;
                 James C. Respess; Audrey K. Brown; Frederic B. Westervelt Jr.; Gilbert Simon;
                 Kenneth R. Crispell; James Q. Miller; Julian R. Beckwith; John A. Owen Jr.; Edmund
                 P. Cawley; John L. Guerrant; G. Slaughter Fitz-Hugh; William R. Sandusky; E. Cato
                 Drash and George Minor; William H. Muller Jr.; Charles J. Frankel; Byrd S.
                 Leavell, William B. Hunt Jr., Daniel N. Mohler, and Carlos R. Ayers; Harry, an
                 unprepared lecture: unknown: William Parson; Fritz E. Dreifuss; Lester F. Stewart;
                 Richard W. Garnett Jr.; Jack D. Hain; L. Gordon Kirschner Jr.; Thomas H. Hunter;
                 Joseph Wolpe; Jerrold E. Hammond.
